Sentencas: In this paper, we propose a new design of flow channel and stack arrangement based on the numerical study considering the effect of the flow channel design on the stack performance and analyze the thermal stress of a planar anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell stack.
Titulo: Numerical modeling of interconnect flow channel design and thermal stress analysis of a planar anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell stack

Sentencas: We also attempt to simplify the cell stack design without affecting its performance and propose an easier sealing method of cell stacks through the study of the thermal stress distribution.
Titulo: Numerical modeling of interconnect flow channel design and thermal stress analysis of a planar anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell stack

Sentencas: The results indicate that the new design, created by changing the cathode flow channel to a porous current collector, with a 6.3% increase in power density.
Titulo: Numerical modeling of interconnect flow channel design and thermal stress analysis of a planar anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell stack
Numerical modeling of interconnect flow channel design and thermal stress analysis of a planar anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell stack

Sentencas: Both more uniform flow and current density distribution can be obtained as compared with a conventional counter-flow design.
Titulo: Numerical modeling of interconnect flow channel design and thermal stress analysis of a planar anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell stack

Sentencas: In addition, we propose a new design direction of cell stack, which could be simpler and easier to fabricate, in which material can easily undertake the resulting stress based on the thermal stress analysis.
Titulo: Numerical modeling of interconnect flow channel design and thermal stress analysis of a planar anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell stack
